    "message_1": "Suppose you are given the following set of data points:\n\nx: 1 2 3 4\n\ny: 5 9 13 15\n\nUsing Lagrange polynomials, find the interpolated value of y when x = 2.5 and the extrapolated value of y when x = 6.",
    "message_2": "To find the interpolated value of y when x = 2.5 and the extrapolated value of y when x = 6 using Lagrange polynomials, we first need to construct the Lagrange polynomial for the given data points.\n\nThe Lagrange polynomial is given by:\n\nL(x) = L_0(x) * y_0 + L_1(x) * y_1 + L_2(x) * y_2 + L_3(x) * y_3\n\nwhere L_i(x) are the Lagrange basis polynomials, defined as:\n\nL_i(x) = Π((x - x_j) / (x_i - x_j)) for j ≠ i\n\nFor the given data points (x_i, y_i):\n\nx_0 = 1, y_0 = 5\nx_1 = 2, y_1 = 9\nx_2 = 3, y_2 = 13\nx_3 = 4, y_3 = 15\n\nNow, we calculate the Lagrange basis polynomials:\n\nL_0(x) = ((x - x_1) * (x - x_2) * (x - x_3)) / ((x_0 - x_1) * (x_0 - x_2) * (x_0 - x_3))\n       = ((x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((1 - 2) * (1 - 3) * (1 - 4))\n       = ((x - 2) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / 6\n\nL_1(x) = ((x - x_0) * (x - x_2) * (x - x_3)) / ((x_1 - x_0) * (x_1 - x_2) * (x_1 - x_3))\n       = ((x - 1) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / ((2 - 1) * (2 - 3) * (2 - 4))\n       = ((x - 1) * (x - 3) * (x - 4)) / (-2)\n\nL_2(x) = ((x - x_0) * (x - x_1) * (x - x_3)) / ((x_2 - x_0) * (x_2 - x_1) * (x_2 - x_3))\n       = ((x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 4)) / ((3 - 1) * (3 - 2) * (3 - 4))\n       = ((x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 4)) / (-2)\n\nL_3(x) = ((x - x_0) * (x - x_1) * (x - x_2)) / ((x_3 - x_0) * (x_3 - x_1) * (x_3 - x_2))\n       = ((x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3)) / ((4 - 1) * (4 - 2) * (4 - 3))\n       = ((x - 1) * (x - 2) * (x - 3)) / 6\n\nNow, we can find the interpolated value of y when x = 2.5:\n\nL(2.5) = L_0(2.5) * y_0 + L_1(2.5) * y_1 + L_2(2.5) * y_2 + L_3(2.5) * y_3\n       = (0.5 * (-0.5) * (-1.5) / 6) * 5 + (1.5 * (-0.5) * (-1.5) / (-2)) * 9 + (1.5 * 0.5 * (-1.5) / (-2)) * 13 + (1.5 * 0.5 * (-0.5) / 6) * 15\n       = 0.25 * 5 - 2.25 * 9 + 1.125 * 13 + 0.25 * 15\n       = 1.25 - 20.25 + 14.625 + 3.75\n       = -0.625\n\nAnd the extrapolated value of y when x = 6:\n\nL(6) = L_0(6) * y_0 + L_1(6) * y_1 + L_2(6) * y_2 + L_3(6) * y_3\n     = (4 * 3 * 2 / 6) * 5 + (5 * 3 * 2 / (-2)) * 9 + (5 * 4 * 2 / (-2)) * 13 + (5 * 4 * 3 / 6) * 15\n     = 12 * 5 - 30 * 9 + 20 * 13 + 10 * 15\n     = 60 - 270 + 260 + 150\n     = 200\n\nSo, the interpolated value of y when x = 2.5 is -0.625, and the extrapolated value of y when x = 6 is 200."
